\f0\b \cf0 |--| midi send
\f1\b0  - is actually not midi send at all but opens a window where you can set loop points.\
\

\f0\b rm
\f1\b0  - removes soundfile from key and clears all settings on that key.\
\

\f0\b killa
\f1\b0  - stops all other sounds playing on the keys, not on sliders or knobs\
\

\f0\b sh
\f1\b0  - "shot", ignores so called 'note off' messages so when you push the key the sound will play to the end of the file even if you stop pressing the key\
