\f0\b \cf0 piano
\f1\b0  - the sound plays for as long as you hold the key down, stops when you release the key\
\

\f0\b shot
\f1\b0  - the sound plays until end of file regardless of releasing the key\
\

\f0\b toggle
\f1\b0  - the sound plays until you push the key down a second time\
\

\f0\b 3 samples
\f1\b0  - this is broken.... or not\
	first sample on green strip is attack\
	sample on key is the loop\
	second sample on green strip is release\
\

\f0\b 2 samples
\f1\b0  - when this is selected a green strip appears to the right of the menu. Drop a soundfile here or shift-click on it to load a second soundfile to be played. The sound loaded at the key (which name is displayed at the key and at the top of the settings part) plays when pushing the key. When releasing the key the first sound stops and the second starts and plays until the end of the sound, unless the key is pushed again, which stops the second sound and starts the first.\
\

\f0\b many
\f1\b0  - this makes it possible to load as many sounds as you want on to one key and play them in sequence, random, or ping-pong (from the first to the last, then reverse back to first), all by hitting one key. If the key is not pushed in 5 seconds the next sound to play is the first. Releasing the key stops the sound unless the 
\f0\b sh
\f1\b0  button is on.\
\
