\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 PitchWheel
\f1\b0\fs24 \
To use the Pitchwheel on the midi keyboard to pitch the sound up and down you need to choose what is going to be pitched. The three buttons top right 
\f0\b SL bnd
\f1\b0 , 
\f0\b KN bnd
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b Ky bnd
\f1\b0 , lets you turn it on or off for Sliders, Knobs and Keys respectively.\
\

\f0\b\fs28 ModWheel
\f1\b0\fs24 \
Right under the bend buttons is the 
\f0\b modWH
\f1\b0  button. Turn this on to control the starting position in the sample with the modulation wheel on the midi keyboard. \
\

\f0\b\fs28 ProgressView (pr view)
\f1\b0\fs24 \
The Progress View is what I call the orange line that moves across the keys as you play a key, indicating how much time is left playing the sound, and similarly on the knobs and sliders with the timer. If for some reason you don't want this showing you can disable/enable it with this button. \
\

\f0\b\fs28 Computer Keyboard to trigger notes
\f1\b0\fs24 \
The KB button lets you use part of the computer keyboard to trigger the first octave or so of the keys.\
\

